        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 7:12PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles west of Westplains to near
Brush, or extending from 29 miles northwest of Sterling to 7 miles
northeast of Fort Morgan, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling, Fort Morgan, Brush, Merino, Hillrose, Pawnee Pass,
Willard, Logan Corners, Stoneham, Atwood, Prewitt Reservoir,
Westplains, North Sterling Reservoir, Antelope Springs, Snyder,
Padroni, Midway, Messex, Union and Fremont Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

Heavy rain is occurring with these storms and may lead to flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
